Class PersistentMap<K extends java.io.Serializable,V extends java.io.Serializable>

  • java.lang.Object
    • io.github.zachohara.bukkit.simpleplugin.persistence.PersistentObject
      • io.github.zachohara.bukkit.simpleplugin.persistence.PersistentMap<K,V>
  • Type Parameters:
    K - the key type of the map
    V - the value type of the map
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.util.Map<K,V>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    PersistentKeyedMap

    public class PersistentMap<K extends java.io.Serializable,V extends java.io.Serializable>
extends PersistentObject
implements java.util.Map<K,V>
    A PersistentMap is responsible for loading and storing any given HashMap object as an external file, so that it remains persistent through server restarts.
    Author:
    Zach Ohara

        Constructs a new PersistentMap with the given plugin as an owner, the data to store, and the filename to store that data to.
        Type Parameters:
        T - any type that is a Map<K, V> and is Serializable.
        Parameters:
        owner - the plugin that created this object.
        data - the serializable Map that should be stored in an external file.
        filename - the filename to store the object as.

      • PersistentMap

        public PersistentMap(SimplePlugin owner,
                     java.lang.String filename)
        Constructs a new PersistentMap with the given plugin as an owner, and the filename to store that data to. This constructor will create a new HashMap object that will contain the data.
        Parameters:
        owner - the plugin that created this object.
        filename - the filename to store the object as.
